answers.body_markdown:
`Task.Run()` wraps your code into the `Task`. The Task is being executed but you need to capture the result of Task execution. So you need to do this:

    var task = Task.Run(async () =&gt; await Connect(MAC, 3));
    
    await task;

But there is no sense to do this. If you want to await your async operation, simply do this:

    await Connect(Mac, 3)

